[src:uv-python/dependencies] The `project.dependencies` and `project.optional-dependencies` fields can be used even if project isn't going to be published.
[src:uv-python/dependencies] `dependency-groups` are a recently standardized feature and may not be supported by all tools yet.
[src:uv-python/dependencies] uv supports modifying the project's dependencies with `uv add` and `uv remove`, but dependency metadata can also be updated by editing the `pyproject.toml` directly.
[src:uv-python/dependencies] The `--dev`, `--group`, or `--optional` flags can be used to add dependencies to an alternative field.
[src:uv-python/dependencies] The dependency will include a constraint, e.g., `>=0.27.2`, for the most recent, compatible version of the package.
[src:uv-python/dependencies] When adding a dependency from a source other than a package registry, uv will add an entry in the sources field.
