[src:uv-python/uv] uv also supports building and publishing projects, even if they're not managed with uv.
[src:uv-python/uv] uv manages dependencies and environments for single-file scripts.
[src:uv-python/uv] uv executes and installs command-line tools provided by Python packages, similar to `pipx`.
[src:uv-python/uv] uv installs Python and allows quickly switching between versions.
[src:uv-python/uv] See the installing Python guide to get started.
[src:uv-python/uv] uv extends their interfaces with advanced features, such as dependency version overrides, platform-independent resolutions, reproducible resolutions, alternative resolution strategies, and more.
[src:uv-python/uv] Migrate to uv without changing your existing workflows — and experience a 10-100x speedup — with the `uv pip` interface.
